Introduction

Chhota Shigri Glacier is located at 3215N 7731E;

Elmer/Ice

Input data sets

Ice thickness

Results from Farinotti et al. (2019) can be downloaded here.

Chhota Shigri Glacier is in region 14 with RGI Id 15590

Raster informations:

  • Projection: +proj=utm +zone=43 +datum=WGS84 +units=m +no_defs +ellps=WGS84 +towgs84=0,0,0
  • Bounding box:
    xmin=730487.50, xmax=739887.50
    ymin=3564912.50, ymax=3572487.50
  • resolution: 25, 25

Save raster in netcdf format:

writeRaster(thk, "ELMER_INPUT_DATA/thk.nc", overwrite=TRUE, format="CDF", varname="thk", varunit="m",longname="thickness", xname="x", yname="y")

Surface DEM

The ASTER GDEM of the area can be downloaded here

Reproject DEM to same grid and proj as thickness:

aster.repro <- projectRaster( from = aster , to = thk , method = "bilinear" )
writeRaster(aster.repro, "ELMER_INPUT_DATA/zs.nc", overwrite=TRUE, format="CDF", varname="zs", varunit="m",longname="elevation", xname="x", yname="y")

Derived products

Bed elevation

Compute the bed elevation as the difference between surface DEM and ice thickness and save as netcdf:

bed <- aster.repro-thk
writeRaster(bed, "ELMER_INPUT_DATA/bedrock.nc", overwrite=TRUE, format="CDF", varname="bed", varunit="m",longname="elevation", xname="x", yname="y")

ice mask

mask <- thk
mask[mask > 0.1] <- 1.0
writeRaster(bed, "ELMER_INPUT_DATA/icemask.nc", overwrite=TRUE, format="CDF", varname="mask", varunit="1",longname="ice_mask", xname="x", yname="y")
